ential vs other D counts), and faceoffs \u2014 and the grade ranks that total against other players at his position over the last three seasons.", "method": "Total WAR sums these four, each priced in wins. The grade is this player's percentile vs same-position peers over the 3-season window."}, "ppOffense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Power-play xG impact (RAPM)", "value": "-0.32 xG/60", "tone": "neg", "strong": true}, {"label": "PP ice time", "value": "78 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the POWER PLAY \u2014 how much his team's chances improve with him on the man advantage, graded only against players who actually log power-play minutes (so a bottom-six grinder isn't penalized for never being out there).", "method": "Power-play expected-goals impact, RAPM-adjusted. Graded vs peers who actually play the PP."}, "pkDefense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Penalty-kill xG suppression (RAPM)", "value": "+0.18 xG/60", "tone": "pos", "strong": true}, {"label": "PK ice time", "value": "55 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the PENALTY KILL \u2014 how well his team smothers chances while short-handed with him on the ice, graded against other penalty-killers.", "method": "Penalty-kill expected-goals suppression, RAPM-adjusted."}, "finishing": {"receipts": [{"label": "Career shots", "value": "344", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals", "value": "44", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals above cell-expected", "value": "+15.6", "tone": "pos"}, {"label": "Finishing / 100 shots", "value": "+1.81", "tone": "pos", "strong": true}, {"label": "95% band", "value": "+0.09 \u2026 +3.53", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Sample", "value": "thin", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "Whether he converts MORE than an average shooter at his position would on the same shots \u2014 with each shot priced by how league shooters actually convert its CONTEXT (danger band \u00d7 strength state \u00d7 rebound), not just its geometry. Trusted more the more he's shot; the ban